WEBVTT

00:00.671 --> 00:02.249
Previously on...

00:02.273 --> 00:03.680
Your spleen has wandered
close to your heart.

00:03.703 --> 00:05.182
We gotta take it out.

00:05.206 --> 00:07.684
Get your insurance
figured out by then, hmm?

00:07.708 --> 00:09.086
There was the bad news...
There's a cop I want you to talk to.

00:09.110 --> 00:12.119
His name is Sullivan. The
file on Noah's daughter.

00:12.143 --> 00:14.191
The discomforting news...

00:14.215 --> 00:16.323
Thanks.

00:16.347 --> 00:18.325
Are you hiding someone
in your house?

00:18.349 --> 00:20.627
Tell me your secrets.
I'll understand. Okay.

00:20.651 --> 00:22.629
And the news
no one should know...

00:22.653 --> 00:24.663
But you tell me yours first.

00:27.558 --> 00:29.036
Once a month,

00:29.060 --> 00:31.038
the crème de la crème
of Fairview society

00:31.062 --> 00:32.779
would attend
a semiformal luncheon

00:32.803 --> 00:36.213
at the home of Maxine Bennett.

00:36.237 --> 00:39.446
Everyone loved
these elegant get-togethers...

00:39.470 --> 00:41.148
Everyone, that is,

00:41.172 --> 00:43.120
but a certain
redheaded housewife

00:43.144 --> 00:46.723
who was convinced
Maxine was a liar.

00:46.747 --> 00:48.725
You see, Maxine liked to brag

00:48.749 --> 00:51.228
that she did
all her own cooking.

00:51.252 --> 00:55.632
And because each course
was served promptly...

00:55.656 --> 00:58.105
Presented with flair...

00:58.129 --> 01:00.067
It's delicious.

01:00.091 --> 01:03.210
And was
positively mouthwatering,

01:03.234 --> 01:06.143
Bree knew Maxine had
had some help.

01:06.167 --> 01:08.145
Thank you so much.

01:08.169 --> 01:10.117
And sadly for Maxine,

01:10.141 --> 01:13.320
Bree intended to prove it.

01:13.344 --> 01:15.687
Maxine, once again,
this entire lunch

01:15.711 --> 01:18.054
was just out of this
world.

01:18.078 --> 01:20.087
I just have to get
the number of your caterer.

01:20.111 --> 01:21.588
What a nice compliment.

01:21.612 --> 01:24.091
No, I'm afraid
this is all my doing.

01:24.115 --> 01:26.193
It was a triumph,
an absolute triumph.

01:26.217 --> 01:29.196
Oh, come on. Do you honestly
expect us to believe

01:29.220 --> 01:32.139
that you had the time to prepare
a 6-course meal for 10 women?

01:32.163 --> 01:33.440
Even I couldn't make this

01:33.464 --> 01:35.681
andhave time
to get ready for a party.

01:35.705 --> 01:39.606
Well, perhaps you're just not
as organized as I am.

01:41.101 --> 01:42.771
If you'll excuse me.

01:44.275 --> 01:46.353
Bree! What's gotten into you?

01:46.377 --> 01:49.156
I have the same recipe
for English plum pudding.

01:49.180 --> 01:51.358
It takes six hours to prepare.

01:51.382 --> 01:53.360
How would she have time
to make all of this

01:53.384 --> 01:55.201
and everything else
that we ate today?

01:55.225 --> 01:58.165
This is not the pudding
of an honest woman.

01:58.189 --> 02:00.197
FBI! Open up!

02:00.221 --> 02:02.399
What on earth?

02:09.699 --> 02:11.678
We're looking
for a Maxine Bennett.

02:11.702 --> 02:14.586
I'm Maxine. We have a warrant
to search the premises, ma'am.

02:14.610 --> 02:17.284
A warrant?
I'm in the middle of a luncheon.

02:17.308 --> 02:18.508
Over here.

02:21.272 --> 02:22.789
Found her.

02:22.813 --> 02:25.121
What?!

02:25.145 --> 02:27.294
Maxine Bennett,
you're under arrest

02:27.318 --> 02:29.896
for involuntary servitude.

02:29.920 --> 02:31.898
Is this the woman
who locked you up?

02:43.163 --> 02:46.513
Bree, what's going on?

02:46.537 --> 02:50.146
Well, I'm not sure,
but I think Maxine had a slave.

02:50.170 --> 02:54.821
I can't believe it.
I just can't believe it.

02:54.845 --> 02:56.483
But Bree could.

02:56.507 --> 02:59.526
You see, for her,

02:59.550 --> 03:07.550
the proof was in the pudding.

03:09.620 --> 03:13.240
The world is filled
with unlikely friendships,

03:13.264 --> 03:17.173
odd pairings,
that to the casual observer,

03:17.197 --> 03:21.208
make absolutely no sense at all.

03:21.232 --> 03:23.710
But if we look closer,

03:23.734 --> 03:27.514
we can see why
these alliances form.

03:27.538 --> 03:29.516
After all, a shared purpose

03:29.540 --> 03:34.391
can give even mortal enemies
common ground.

03:34.415 --> 03:36.393
Bree?
We have a question for you.

03:36.417 --> 03:37.894
Oh! What is it?

03:37.918 --> 03:39.896
Well, we were just wondering...

03:39.920 --> 03:42.198
Actually, we were curious
about, um...

03:42.222 --> 03:45.939
What the hell's going on with you
and Betty applewhite? Yeah, that.

03:45.963 --> 03:47.274
Excuse me?

03:47.298 --> 03:49.276
Well, from the day
that dead body showed up,

03:49.300 --> 03:51.608
nobody was yelling, "oh,
the applewhites are involved!"

03:51.632 --> 03:53.310
Louder than you.

03:53.334 --> 03:54.917
And the next thing we know,

03:54.941 --> 03:56.913
you're having Betty over
for poker. What gives?

03:56.937 --> 04:00.617
She makes it sound like we're angry,
and we're not angry. I'm a little angry.

04:00.641 --> 04:03.490
Can we talk about this later?
I-I have ice cream in here.

04:03.514 --> 04:05.961
Bree, could this flip-flop have
something to do with the fact

04:05.985 --> 04:08.325
that Danielle is dating Matthew?

04:08.349 --> 04:10.257
I knew that would get her.

04:10.281 --> 04:12.329
Who told you that?

04:12.353 --> 04:15.507
Mrs. Mcclusky. She saw them
making out in the park. Edie!

04:15.531 --> 04:17.764
What? Can't you
sugarcoat it a little?

04:17.788 --> 04:18.935
I did.

04:18.959 --> 04:22.007
He had his hand
down her shirt.

04:22.031 --> 04:24.376
Bree, we know
that you have a good reason

04:24.400 --> 04:26.373
for wanting Betty
to hang out with us.

04:26.397 --> 04:29.476
We just... wondered if you
could clue us in a little.

04:29.500 --> 04:31.478
When it comes
to Betty applewhite,

04:31.502 --> 04:32.979
I know what I'm doing,

04:33.003 --> 04:36.523
and you two are just
gonna have to trust me.

04:36.547 --> 04:38.024
And if you can't do that,

04:38.048 --> 04:40.387
then perhaps I've overestimated
the depth of our friendship.

04:40.411 --> 04:41.888
Now, if you'll excuse me...

04:41.912 --> 04:43.860
What a bitch.

04:43.884 --> 04:45.992
Edie, can you...

04:46.016 --> 04:47.686
Iwassugarcoating it.

04:55.896 --> 04:57.504
Hey.

04:57.528 --> 04:58.575
Oh! Hi.

04:58.599 --> 05:01.277
Hey, none of that in here.

05:01.301 --> 05:03.580
Come on. Maybe if we remind ed
that I'm shacking up

05:03.604 --> 05:06.461
with the senior v.P., he'll stop
killing all my pitches.

05:06.485 --> 05:08.485
You've only been here a week.

05:08.509 --> 05:11.488
Why don't you give yourself a break? Honey,
you know the ad game.

05:11.512 --> 05:14.060
I've only got a certain amount
of time to make my Mark

05:14.084 --> 05:16.067
before he kicks me to the curb.

05:16.091 --> 05:18.495
Look, I'm just asking you...
Jump in every once in a while,

05:18.519 --> 05:21.498
throw me some rope, you know, when
Ed's on the warpath. I can't protect you.

05:21.522 --> 05:24.336
You're gonna have to find a way
to click with ed yourself.

05:24.360 --> 05:27.374
And then the pig... he rubs his
stomach and he goes...

05:27.398 --> 05:29.376
"Farm fresh bacon

05:29.400 --> 05:31.738
will make a piggy out of you,
too."

05:37.007 --> 05:38.745
So...

05:38.769 --> 05:41.588
The pig actually eats the bacon?

05:41.612 --> 05:44.529
Uh-huh, yeah. I don't see
the client doing a happy dance

05:44.553 --> 05:47.075
over the whole
cannibalism theme.

05:49.049 --> 05:51.528
Well, Tom, why don't
you pitch him the other idea

05:51.552 --> 05:55.036
you came up with last night?
You know, the one where

05:55.060 --> 05:57.764
people love bacon so much
they wanna keep it a secret?

05:57.788 --> 05:59.706
What, like a secret underground
society of bacon eaters?

05:59.730 --> 06:01.768
More like my college fraternity,
where, you know,

06:01.792 --> 06:05.079
everybody wanted in, but we only
took the coolest guys.

06:05.103 --> 06:07.514
Wait, you were Greek?

06:07.538 --> 06:09.716
Yeah, Alpha tau omega.

06:09.740 --> 06:11.448
I was phi kapp. You?

06:11.472 --> 06:14.350
And I don't remember you having
to be that cool to pledge a.T.O.

06:14.374 --> 06:17.584
Look, if I had a nickel
for every phi kapp

06:17.608 --> 06:20.427
that I tied naked
to a freeway sign...

06:20.451 --> 06:23.059
Scavo, if you were my pledge, I'd have
made you my bitch. Oh, you think so?

06:23.083 --> 06:26.663
You know what? I'm liking
this whole fraternity angle.

06:28.419 --> 06:31.398
Yeah. You know what?
Let's talk about it over lunch.

06:31.422 --> 06:33.822
You're buying.

06:34.965 --> 06:37.125
Go.

06:40.571 --> 06:41.848
Thanks for your help.

06:48.779 --> 06:50.817
Hello. What's going on?

06:50.841 --> 06:53.520
Gabrielle,
I want you to meet someone.

06:53.544 --> 06:55.462
This is xiao-Mei.

06:55.486 --> 06:57.464
She's the young lady
who was forced to work

06:57.488 --> 06:59.796
for Maxine Bennett.
Oh, the slave.

06:59.820 --> 07:03.399
Wow. Looks well-fed.

07:03.423 --> 07:05.440
The church
is making arrangements

07:05.464 --> 07:07.434
for her to return to China.

07:07.458 --> 07:08.575
But until then,
she needs a place to stay.

07:08.599 --> 07:11.037
So I offered up our guest room.

07:11.061 --> 07:13.580
Really?

07:13.604 --> 07:16.621
Baby, can I talk
to you for a second?

07:16.645 --> 07:19.015
Ahem.

07:19.039 --> 07:20.517
Are you nuts?!

07:20.541 --> 07:22.919
It's only for a couple of days. Oh,
thistime.

07:22.943 --> 07:24.420
You are quickly becoming

07:24.444 --> 07:26.528
father crowley's go-to guy
for charity cases.

07:26.552 --> 07:28.755
And that's a bad thing?
When he turns our house

07:28.779 --> 07:31.027
into a catholic
underground railroad, yes!

07:31.051 --> 07:34.030
You know who you are, Gaby?
You're the kind of person

07:34.054 --> 07:37.041
who would've turned away
Mary and Joseph from the inn.

07:37.065 --> 07:39.606
Well, they should've
called ahead.

07:47.498 --> 07:49.776
Don't brush your hair
at the table.

07:49.800 --> 07:51.918
Oh, you're talking to me?

07:51.942 --> 07:53.920
Does this mean
you've finally forgiven me?

07:53.944 --> 07:55.552
Why should I?

07:55.576 --> 07:57.554
You betrayed this family,
and you're not even sorry.

07:57.578 --> 07:59.486
Don't be such a drama queen.

07:59.510 --> 08:01.187
If the applewhites
go to the police

08:01.211 --> 08:04.861
and tell them that your brother
ran over Mrs. Solis,

08:04.885 --> 08:07.093
he could go to prison.

08:07.117 --> 08:09.095
How can you not understand that?

08:09.119 --> 08:10.597
They won't talk about Andrew

08:10.621 --> 08:13.199
as long as you don't go
to the police about Caleb.

08:13.223 --> 08:15.206
What did this Caleb do, exactly?

08:15.230 --> 08:17.544
And why on earth
are they hiding him?

08:17.568 --> 08:19.546
Why don't you go
to Mrs. Applewhite

08:19.570 --> 08:22.649
and tell her you really need
to know what's going on?

08:22.673 --> 08:25.216
I bet if you were really nice,
she'd tell you the truth.

08:25.240 --> 08:27.714
Is that what
you really think, Danielle?

08:27.738 --> 08:30.517
I should go
to Mrs. Applewhite, be nice,

08:30.541 --> 08:33.860
and then she'll hand over
all her secrets?

08:33.884 --> 08:35.692
Yeah.

08:35.716 --> 08:40.667
When I was young, my stepmother
told me that I was very lucky.

08:40.691 --> 08:45.872
I possessed beauty,
wit, cunning and insight.

08:45.896 --> 08:50.677
These were weapons all women
needed to survive in the world.

08:50.701 --> 08:52.609
So?

08:52.633 --> 08:55.286
So take good care
of your looks, Danielle.

08:55.310 --> 08:57.805
You don't have any other weapons
at your disposal.

09:05.175 --> 09:07.994
Hi. I need an operation
on my spleen,

09:08.018 --> 09:10.697
and I just found out
I don't have medical insurance.

09:10.721 --> 09:13.159
Is there anyone I can sue?

09:13.183 --> 09:16.207
After the embezzlement,
lonny let the policy lapse.

09:16.231 --> 09:18.765
And now he's in jail,
and I'm gonna die.

09:18.789 --> 09:20.266
Susie, you're not gonna die.

09:20.290 --> 09:23.169
I'll get into it
with the insurance company.

09:23.193 --> 09:25.677
No, there isn't time for you
to deal with the red tape.

09:25.701 --> 09:28.244
My spleen is going careening
into my heart.

09:28.268 --> 09:31.978
I need that operation now. Yeah,
I'd loan you the money myself,

09:32.002 --> 09:34.080
but Edie and I just
plopped down our savings

09:34.104 --> 09:35.582
in a ski condo and...

09:35.606 --> 09:39.125
I don't need a loan.
I need coverage.

09:39.149 --> 09:41.728
I mean, what if there
are complications?

09:41.752 --> 09:43.730
I don't have a safety net.

09:43.754 --> 09:46.032
Oh, my god, please!

09:46.056 --> 09:48.665
What in the hell are you doing?

09:48.689 --> 09:50.266
I'm saying a little prayer.

09:50.290 --> 09:51.838
Oh, for puke's sake...

09:51.862 --> 09:54.809
Well, what? I'm desperate here.
Do you have any other ideas?

09:54.833 --> 09:57.203
As a matter of fact, I do.

09:57.227 --> 09:59.205
What you need is a husband.

09:59.229 --> 10:00.777
What?

10:00.801 --> 10:03.109
The only way
to get a good health plan

10:03.133 --> 10:04.811
is to marry into one.

10:04.835 --> 10:06.983
Edie, come on.

10:07.007 --> 10:08.985
No, no, I think
she's onto something.

10:09.009 --> 10:12.058
Yeah. If we find a guy
with the right plan,

10:12.082 --> 10:14.766
you could have a sham wedding
on a Monday night

10:14.790 --> 10:16.793
and be fully covered
Tuesday morning.

10:16.817 --> 10:19.696
I can't believe you're
actually considering this.

10:19.720 --> 10:21.998
The surgeon is slicing me open
a week from tomorrow.

10:22.022 --> 10:24.600
What other choice do I have?

10:24.624 --> 10:27.964
All we have to do is find a guy
who's willing to marry you.

10:31.732 --> 10:33.710
You know, come to think of it,

10:33.734 --> 10:36.844
a little prayer might not be
such a bad idea after all.

10:47.377 --> 10:48.855
Pat, we're all here,

10:48.879 --> 10:52.349
so send the call in
as soon as you get it.

10:54.855 --> 10:58.835
200 bucks says you can't do that
3 times in a row.

10:58.859 --> 11:00.937
Huh?

11:00.961 --> 11:03.269
You catch three of those...

11:03.293 --> 11:04.671
200 bucks.

11:04.695 --> 11:06.743
What do you say there, Scavo?

11:06.767 --> 11:09.816
You're on.

11:09.840 --> 11:11.678
Here we go. Ah-ah-ah-ah!

11:11.702 --> 11:13.419
Thrown byme.

11:13.443 --> 11:15.430
I'm sorry,
I thought we were here

11:15.454 --> 11:18.184
to talk about
the farm fresh rollout?

11:18.208 --> 11:21.788
They gotta be catchable, big guy.
You just let me worry about the shooting.

11:21.812 --> 11:22.812
Come on.

11:25.716 --> 11:27.363
That's one.

11:27.387 --> 11:28.387
Guys...

11:29.820 --> 11:31.798
Oh!

11:31.822 --> 11:32.999
Nice moves.

11:33.023 --> 11:35.050
One more, big guy.
Guys, please...

11:35.074 --> 11:36.695
That's... all right.

11:38.729 --> 11:39.776
Ow!

11:39.800 --> 11:42.278
Oh!

11:42.302 --> 11:43.679
Ow.

11:43.703 --> 11:46.387
That wasn't even catchable!
Yeah, well, maybe not.

11:46.411 --> 11:49.115
But it's totally worth
the 200 bucks. Ahh!

11:49.139 --> 11:50.116
Whoo!

11:50.140 --> 11:52.118
Well, you got me.

11:52.142 --> 11:54.120
You're a regular
little monkey man!

11:54.144 --> 11:56.154
Oh, I love this guy.

12:03.053 --> 12:05.233
Oh. Hi.

12:07.828 --> 12:09.806
Do you have to sit around
all day?

12:09.830 --> 12:11.808
I mean, shouldn't you be out

12:11.832 --> 12:13.109
experiencing
western civilization

12:13.133 --> 12:15.842
while you have the chance?

12:15.866 --> 12:18.314
What are you doing?

12:18.338 --> 12:19.445
I fix.

12:19.469 --> 12:21.117
No, this is couture!

12:21.141 --> 12:23.920
This rip has to be fixed
by an experienced tailor.

12:23.944 --> 12:25.421
You can't just...

12:25.445 --> 12:27.824
Holy crap!
This stitching is perfect!

12:27.848 --> 12:29.848
Hungry?

12:35.255 --> 12:37.425
Did you make all of this?

12:39.790 --> 12:41.137
Oh!

12:41.161 --> 12:44.461
For me? Okay.

12:48.839 --> 12:50.116
Oh, my god!

12:50.140 --> 12:51.878
You like?

12:51.902 --> 12:53.542
I like a lot.

13:07.517 --> 13:09.495
You like that?

13:09.519 --> 13:11.838
Yeah, that's nice.

13:11.862 --> 13:14.140
Do you know what they do
to people in China

13:14.164 --> 13:16.147
who speak out against
the government? Hmm?

13:16.171 --> 13:18.144
They put them
in forced labor camps.

13:18.168 --> 13:19.775
Isn't that awful?

13:19.799 --> 13:21.107
Mm-hmm.

13:21.131 --> 13:24.510
You know what I mean?
It's such a repressive regime.

13:24.534 --> 13:26.521
We forget how good we have it.

13:26.545 --> 13:29.055
Yes, we do.

13:29.079 --> 13:30.917
Don't you think xiao-Mei

13:30.941 --> 13:33.389
would like it better here
in america?

13:33.413 --> 13:35.391
I mean, where she could learn

13:35.415 --> 13:38.825
about freedom and democracy
and stuff?

13:38.849 --> 13:40.827
Does this have anything to do

13:40.851 --> 13:42.969
with you making xiao-Mei
do housework?

13:42.993 --> 13:45.410
What? I came downstairs this
morning and found her waxing the floor.

13:45.434 --> 13:48.274
She told me you asked her
to put on two coats.

13:48.298 --> 13:51.107
Well, first of all,
that was her idea.

13:51.131 --> 13:53.109
Second of all,
I can't have this conversation

13:53.133 --> 13:56.013
until you've tasted
her crab puffs. Oh...

13:58.168 --> 14:00.216
Hmm. Mmm.

14:00.240 --> 14:02.818
She just got done being a slave.

14:02.842 --> 14:05.992
I mean, she wants
to go back to China...

14:06.016 --> 14:07.994
And we can't force her
to stay here and be our maid.

14:08.018 --> 14:09.495
Well, who's forcing her?

14:09.519 --> 14:11.497
We'll pay her
whatever she wants.

14:11.521 --> 14:14.130
And the best part is,
with her résumé,

14:14.154 --> 14:16.132
anywage will look good.

14:16.156 --> 14:17.856
No way, baby. Mnh-mnh.

14:19.129 --> 14:20.106
Hmm.

14:20.130 --> 14:21.437
What?

14:21.461 --> 14:23.910
What?

14:23.934 --> 14:26.221
What, so you don't get
what you want,

14:26.245 --> 14:28.214
you just walk off and pout?

14:28.238 --> 14:31.317
Oh, this isn't about me.
This is about our great nation.

14:31.341 --> 14:33.880
And I have no intention
of sexually satisfying a man

14:33.904 --> 14:35.887
who isn't willing
to stand up for

14:35.911 --> 14:37.884
and help spread
the ideals and values

14:37.908 --> 14:40.008
of the United States of america.

14:43.553 --> 14:45.536
And sometimes sheis
a little hard to stomach,

14:45.560 --> 14:47.533
but she means well.
Well, that's...

14:47.557 --> 14:49.535
Hi! Oh, here she is.

14:49.559 --> 14:52.068
I came as soon as I got
your message. Is this...

14:52.092 --> 14:53.900
This is Gary grantham,
your future ex-husband.

14:53.924 --> 14:56.342
Wow, nice to meet you. Hi.

14:56.366 --> 14:58.344
Okay, listen, um,
I've got to meet a client.

14:58.368 --> 15:00.406
I've got to go,
so just talk amongst yourselves,

15:00.430 --> 15:03.409
and you two make
a very handsome couple.

15:03.433 --> 15:04.450
Oh.

15:04.474 --> 15:07.453
Yeah.

15:07.477 --> 15:10.156
Uh, hi. Hi.

