Shave my eyebrows?
Come to work naked?

33:30.439 --> 33:32.117
Name your stakes.

33:32.141 --> 33:35.620
I don't have time for this. Aw,
what's wrong, ed?

33:35.644 --> 33:39.294
You afraid a phi kapp's
gonna get beaten by a girl?

33:39.318 --> 33:41.096
Come on, big man...

33:41.120 --> 33:43.120
It's just a little bet.

33:47.796 --> 33:51.236
As you know, I think
that making the workplace fun

33:51.260 --> 33:52.737
is good for morale.

33:52.761 --> 33:56.141
But Lynette here thinks
that our shenanigans

33:56.165 --> 33:57.382
have gotten
a little out of hand.

33:57.406 --> 34:00.085
Oh, hold on.

34:00.109 --> 34:02.587
Hold on. I respect
Lynette's work ethic.

34:02.611 --> 34:05.019
So we've decided
to settle the matter

34:05.043 --> 34:09.724
with a little test
of intestinal fortitude.

34:09.748 --> 34:13.058
If she can eat 1 pound

34:13.081 --> 34:18.063
of our client's fine,
farm-fresh pork product, raw...

34:20.389 --> 34:23.538
There'll be a moratorium
on wagering in the office.

34:23.562 --> 34:25.469
Oh, oh!

34:25.494 --> 34:27.281
I know
you are doing this for me.

34:27.304 --> 34:29.614
You don't need to do this.

34:29.638 --> 34:32.177
I don't need you fighting my
fights. I am not fighting your fights.

34:32.201 --> 34:34.179
This is my fight.

34:34.203 --> 34:36.186
This is how guys
do business, right?

34:36.210 --> 34:37.745
I gotta see this.

34:44.652 --> 34:46.731
This is so disgusting.

34:46.755 --> 34:48.554
We're counting on you.

34:51.159 --> 34:53.460
While we're young.

35:04.433 --> 35:07.282
No shame in defeat, Lynette.

35:07.306 --> 35:09.176
No shame at all.

35:23.121 --> 35:24.851
Oh, she's gonna do it.

35:29.298 --> 35:31.198
Ohh!

35:33.262 --> 35:35.262
Oh, yes!

35:38.367 --> 35:40.207
Oh!

35:50.449 --> 35:53.219
Oh, this is too much.

35:56.725 --> 35:58.463
Oh!

35:59.588 --> 36:04.439
What? She took the bet.

36:04.463 --> 36:07.643
What? This isfun, people.

36:09.167 --> 36:11.145
She's got one more.

36:31.490 --> 36:37.372
So... can this be a place
of business again, ed?

36:37.396 --> 36:39.244
No more games?

36:39.268 --> 36:40.268
Sure.

36:41.370 --> 36:43.870
You sucked all the fun
out of it anyway.

36:46.375 --> 36:48.383
Lynette...

36:48.407 --> 36:50.537
I gotta go back to work.

36:53.442 --> 36:57.492
Thatwas really something.

36:57.516 --> 36:59.894
Thanks.

36:59.918 --> 37:02.748
Could you scrounge me up
a bucket?

37:15.804 --> 37:17.791
Caleb said
a nice, red-haired lady

37:17.815 --> 37:19.284
came to visit him.

37:19.308 --> 37:20.968
Come on in, Betty.

37:25.514 --> 37:27.522
Get you a drink?

37:27.546 --> 37:29.524
This is not a social call, Bree!

37:29.548 --> 37:32.457
Did you or did you not break
into my home and talk to my son?

37:32.481 --> 37:35.960
Caleb and I had, uh,
a very lovely chat. Yes.

37:35.984 --> 37:38.241
If you ever
come near him again,

37:38.265 --> 37:40.305
there will be hell to pay.

37:40.329 --> 37:41.829
Do you understand?

37:43.892 --> 37:46.279
Aren't you gonna ask me
what we talked about?

37:46.303 --> 37:48.773
The name, um...

37:48.797 --> 37:51.397
Melanie foster came up.

37:54.343 --> 37:56.656
I'm gonna pour you
a drink now, Betty,

37:56.680 --> 37:59.724
because we're about to have
a very honest discussion,

37:59.748 --> 38:02.457
and I think you're gonna
need a little help

38:02.481 --> 38:04.351
getting through it.

38:07.456 --> 38:10.895
His name's Zach young.
He lives with his father.

38:10.919 --> 38:13.368
Mother committed suicide
about a year ago.

38:13.392 --> 38:15.440
How did he end up
with these people?

38:15.464 --> 38:16.941
How do you think?

38:16.965 --> 38:19.944
Dierdre was strung out, Noah.
She gave him up.

38:19.968 --> 38:22.447
I wanna see this boy.

38:22.471 --> 38:24.449
Well, he's got a new family now.

38:24.473 --> 38:26.456
I can't just snap my fingers
and get him in here.

38:26.480 --> 38:28.453
Maybe not,
but I can snap my fingers,

38:28.477 --> 38:31.316
and detective Sullivan can make
it happen. You don't wanna do that.

38:31.340 --> 38:34.319
No? Is that really the
way you wanna meet him...

38:34.343 --> 38:37.427
Have that thug drag him in here
so grandpa can give him a hug?

38:37.451 --> 38:40.325
Fine. You bring him.
I'll give you two days.

38:40.349 --> 38:43.349
As you know, I'm on a bit
of a clock here.

38:50.359 --> 38:51.936
When Caleb was born,

38:51.960 --> 38:56.080
and the doctors discovered
that he was different,

38:56.104 --> 38:57.774
I didn't even cry.

39:00.809 --> 39:05.920
It wasthemost painful moment
of my life.

39:05.944 --> 39:08.322
I didn't shed a single tear.

39:08.346 --> 39:12.026
I just thought to myself,
what's the point?

39:12.050 --> 39:18.963
He is my son, and I have
to raise him as best I can.

39:18.987 --> 39:21.127
Now that's my job.

39:22.591 --> 39:25.540
In a lot of ways,
I feel so blessed.

39:25.564 --> 39:31.015
Calebischallenged,
but he has such a sweet nature.

39:31.039 --> 39:34.379
I'm sure you noticed that
when you came to visit.

39:34.403 --> 39:36.043
Yes, I did.

39:37.746 --> 39:41.446
I also noticed that you had him
chained in the basement.

39:44.613 --> 39:46.993
That's because
of Melanie foster.

39:49.387 --> 39:54.469
Melanie was a girl
that Matthew dated.

39:54.493 --> 39:57.472
She was a debutante.

39:57.496 --> 39:59.644
And like typical teenagers,

39:59.668 --> 40:02.607
their relationship
was full of drama.

40:02.631 --> 40:05.410
They were always breaking up
and getting back together

40:05.434 --> 40:06.711
and breaking up.

40:06.735 --> 40:10.384
One night, after one
of their big blow-ups,

40:10.408 --> 40:12.487
Caleb somehow convinced Melanie

40:12.511 --> 40:15.460
to meet him down
at our local lumberyard.

40:15.484 --> 40:18.571
I can only imagine that
she thought he was bringing

40:18.595 --> 40:23.528
some kind of apology
from Matthew, but he wasn't.

40:23.552 --> 40:27.772
Caleb told Melanie
he was in love with her,

40:27.796 --> 40:30.905
and that
if he was her boyfriend,

40:30.929 --> 40:34.839
he would never
break up with her...

40:34.863 --> 40:37.542
And she laughed in his face.

40:37.566 --> 40:43.017
He tried to show her
he was serious by kissing her...

40:43.041 --> 40:46.441
And she hit him.

40:49.047 --> 40:52.026
He doesn't remember a lot
of what happened after that,

40:52.050 --> 40:56.731
but he... he does know that
he got very, very angry, and...

40:56.755 --> 41:00.125
And that there was an ax
lying on the ground nearby him.

41:04.593 --> 41:09.674
Yes, my Caleb killed Melanie,

41:09.698 --> 41:13.548
but I couldn't
let him go to jail...

41:13.572 --> 41:17.552
Or worse, be put down,

41:17.576 --> 41:20.685
for what was really my crime.

41:20.709 --> 41:22.579
Your crime?

41:25.584 --> 41:28.893
It was my responsibility.

41:28.917 --> 41:31.736
I was supposed
to protect him from himself.

41:31.760 --> 41:34.739
I am his mother.

41:34.763 --> 41:37.003
That was my job.

41:49.137 --> 41:55.019
The world is filled
with unlikely friendships.

41:55.043 --> 41:57.522
How do they begin?

41:57.546 --> 42:00.525
With one person
desperately in need,

42:00.549 --> 42:05.600
and another willing to lend
a helping hand.

42:05.624 --> 42:08.037
When such kindness is
offered... Whoo!

42:08.061 --> 42:10.174
We're finally able
to see the worth

42:10.198 --> 42:15.610
of those
we had previously written off.

42:15.634 --> 42:17.912
And before we know it...

42:17.936 --> 42:20.685
A bond has formed,

42:20.709 --> 42:25.890
regardless of whether others
can understand it.

42:25.914 --> 42:30.625
Yes, unlikely friendships
start up every day.

42:30.649 --> 42:33.057
No one understands this

42:33.081 --> 42:36.121
more than the lonely.

42:37.656 --> 42:39.533
In fact,

42:39.557 --> 42:41.557
it's what they count on.
